frameDefinitions: An Agent disables a flying or floating Patient, causing it to be unable to support itself in its current medium.
A Winner has victory over an Loser.
This frame concerns people being in an altered mental state that is induced by an Intoxicant.
An Agent begins preventing a Captive from moving despite a tendency or desire on the part of the Captive to do so.
A Killer or Cause causes the death of the Victim.
frameExamples: It's rumored that she <t>downed</t> a helicopter with a precisely fired arrow.
Authorities recently <t>captured</t> several suspects who were hiding in a remote mountain area.
